Ms. Susan Tait confirmed that she found her daughter, Sue-Allen, on the afternoon bus yesterday afternoon. Sue-Allen was last seen when she got onto the school bus bound for W H de Klerk on Friday morning. She had arranged with her mother to visit a friend after school on Friday afternoon but would have returned the same day to her home in Mineralia. Also read: Teen missing since Friday Sue-Allen was not seen or heard of afterwards and failed to attend school on Monday. Ms. Tait was relieved to report that her daughter returned home on yesterday’s afternoon bus and thanked everyone for their help in her daughter’s search. Also read: Young teen fails to show up at school, search continues